HEADWORD: Staphylorrhaphy
<hw>Staph`y*lor"rha*phy</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(-l⟦ocr⟧r"⟦adot⟧*f⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>stafylh`</grk> the uvula when swollen + <grk>"ra`ptein</grk> to
sew: cf. F. <ets>staphylorraphie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>
<def>The operation of uniting a cleft palate, consisting in paring and
bringing together the edges of the cleft.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Staph`y*lo*raph"ic</wf>
<pr>(st⟦acr⟧f`⟦icr⟧*l⟦osl⟧*r⟦acr⟧f"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
